### Configure Document Scanner Options

Source: https://context7.com/dariyd/react-native-document-scanner/llms.txt

Defines the configuration object for controlling scanner behavior and output format. Options include image quality and whether to include base64 encoding. Defaults are sensible, making all options optional.

```typescript
interface ScanOptions {
  quality?: number;         // 0.0 to 1.0, default: 1.0
  includeBase64?: boolean;  // default: false
}

// Example: High-quality scan without base64 (minimal memory usage)
const highQuality = await launchScanner({
  quality: 1.0,
  includeBase64: false
});

// Example: Compressed scan with base64 (for immediate upload)
const compressed = await launchScanner({
  quality: 0.6,
  includeBase64: true
});
// iOS: quality < 1.0 outputs JPEG, quality = 1.0 outputs PNG
// Android: always outputs JPEG regardless of quality setting
```
